evision','',0),(255,3,'2016-10-11 16:06:49','2016-10-11 05:06:49','<h2>Introducing your new VIP card</h2>\r\nOne membership card- thousands of benefits!\r\n\r\nWhether you are dining out, servicing you car, shopping or seeing a movie you’ll save again and again with your Rewards Club membership card. Combined with your Dapto Leagues Club &amp; The Grange Golf Club membership card is now also a Rewards Club Members.\r\n\r\nBy simply showing your Dapto Leagues Rewards club card you will have access to VIP benefits at hundreds of local retails including:\r\nSubway | Hoyts | Domino’s Pizza | Video Ezy | Bakers Delight | Rebel Sport | Beach Street | Keira Dry Cleaners | and more\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Enjoy all the benefits the club has to offer!</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>As a Dapto Leagues Club &amp; Grange Golf Club Member, you will gain access to our extensive Club Facilities including cafe’s, restaurants, bars, entertainment and promotions.</li>\r\n 	<li>At Dapto Leagues, you can join in our Weekly raffles, Monthly Birthday Offers and Draws, Members Draw which is $5000 1st Wednesday of the Month plus the chance to win 5 x $100 every Wednesday (LTPS/13/10408)</li>\r\n 	<li>Plus receive 10% off food and beverage purchases at Dapto Leagues &amp; The Grange Golf Club (excludes Treasure Court)</li>\r\n 	<li>Save 5% when purchasing WISH cards for participating stores from reception.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nStores include: Woolworth’s Supermarkets | Caltex Woolworthâ’s outlets | Big W | Dick Smith | Woolworth’s Liquor | Tandy | BWS','Membership','','inherit','closed','closed','','52-revision-v1','','','2016-10-11 16:06:49','2016-10-11 05:06:49','',52,'http://thegrangegolfclub.com.au/52-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(256,3,'2016-10-11 16:08:07','2016-10-11 05:08:07','<h2>The Grange Golf Club tees up Troon with $7m make-over</h2>\r\nThe world’s largest golf management company set to deliver a new golfing and events experience to the Illawarra\r\n\r\nIllawarra, NSW, 1st June, 2016 – The NSW South Coast’s leading golf club, The Grange, and amalgamated events partner, Dapto Leagues, has today signed an exclusive deal with Troon®, the leader in upscale golf facility management, development and marketing, as part of a strategic $7m refurbishment of the Grange clubhouse, function facilities and golf course.\r\n\r\nTroon is the largest third party golf management company in the world and will be working to the objectives set out by The Grange and Dapto Leagues board to help ensure continued prosperity, membership loyalty and growth for the club.\r\n\r\nIn addition, Troon aims to drive golf tourism to NSW’s South Coast, boosting the Ilawarra’s regional economy through its global club network of 200 clubs currently under management worldwide.\r\nGary Tozer, Club President at Dapto Leagues and The Grange, said the deal represents a new era for the club, “Over the past 50 years, The Grange has grown to become the foremost golf club in Wollongong and the Illawarra region. As part of our ongoing strategy to strive for better customer experience, we’re already underway improving our clubhouse, the events facilities and the golf course itself.\r\n“Our aim is to continue to be the finest community sport and leisure destination for the people of the Illawarra, whilst appealing to wider audiences, encouraging social activities and for golf enthusiasts, improving the course layout to challenge our loyal golf members and new visitors alike”.\r\nCommenting on the new partnership, Bruce Glasco Chief Operating Officer, Managing Director, Troon International Division added, “The Grange and Dapto League’s approach to continually improving customer experience is a mirror of Troon’s own commitment to supporting the communities around our clubs. Simply put, The Grange presented us with the opportunity for a perfect partnership as Troon brings a wealth of experience managing over 200 clubs worldwide”.\r\nStage one of the development programme has commenced, with the new club house, pro shop, amenities, bar and café, 200 guest function room, gardens and front entrance due for completion in late 2016.\r\nDavid Hiscox CEO of Dapto Leagues and The Grange concluded, “Our ambitious project to invest in renovation, expansion and improved course design will elevate the club beyond public expectations. The revitalised club will expand its appeal to cater for everyone’s needs on and off the course from weddings to conferences, not to mention attract additional golf tourism to the South of NSW boosting the local economy.”\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>For further information, contact:</strong>\r\n<strong>Jordan Cameron, Toast Creative, Jordan@toastcreative.com.au, 0403 000 865</strong>\r\n<strong>Euan Blake, Toast Creative. euan@toastcreative.com.au, 0499 772 639</strong>\r\n','Club House','','inherit','closed','closed','','50-revision-v1','','','2016-10-11 16:08:07','2016-10-11 05:08:07','',50,'http://thegrangegolfclub.com.au/50-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(257,3,'2016-10-11 16:08:34','2016-10-11 05:08:34','<h2>The Grange Golf Club tees up Troon with $7m make-over</h2>\r\nThe world’s largest golf management company set to deliver a new golfing and events experience to the Illawarra\r\n\r\nIllawarra, NSW, 1st June, 2016 – The NSW South Coast’s leading golf club, The Grange, and amalgamated events partner, Dapto Leagues, has today signed an exclusive deal with Troon®, the leader in upscale golf facility management, development and marketing, as part of a strategic $7m refurbishment of the Grange clubhouse, function facilities and golf course.\r\n\r\nTroon is the largest third party golf management company in the world and will be working to the objectives set out by The Grange and Dapto Leagues board to help ensure continued prosperity, membership loyalty and growth for the club.\r\n\r\nIn addition, Troon aims to drive golf tourism to NSW’s South Coast, boosting the Ilawarra’s regional economy through its global club network of 200 clubs currently under manag